  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I find online jobs that pay for real?",
  "response": "There are many legitimate websites where you can find online jobs that pay well. Here are some popular platforms to consider:\n\n1. **Freelance Websites**:\n   - **Upwork**: Connects freelancers with businesses looking for services like writing, design, programming, and more.\n   - **Fiverr**: Allows freelancers to offer services starting at $5 in various categories.\n   - **Freelancer**: Similar to Upwork, it offers a wide range of job postings for freelancers.\n\n2. **Remote Job Boards**:\n   - **We Work Remotely**: A platform specifically for remote job listings across various industries.\n   - **Remote.co**: Lists remote jobs for various professionals, from customer service to advanced tech roles.\n   - **FlexJobs**: A subscription service that curates flexible job listings, including remote and freelance work.\n\n3. **Traditional Job Websites**:\n   - **Indeed**: Allows you to filter job searches for remote work.\n   - **Glassdoor**: Provides company reviews and salary information along with job listings.\n   - **LinkedIn**: A professional networking site where you can find remote job postings and network with recruiters.\n\n4. **Specialized Websites**:\n   - **AngelList**: Focuses on startup job listings, many of which offer remote positions, especially in tech.\n   - **GitHub Jobs**: For tech and programming jobs, you can find remote opportunities specifically geared towards developers.\n   - **Working Nomads**: Curates remote job listings across various categories.\n\n5. **Gig Economy Platforms**:\n   - **TaskRabbit**: Offers various short-term jobs that can sometimes be done remotely.\n   - **Tutoring Platforms**: Websites like **VIPKid** or **Wyzant** allow you to teach or tutor students online.\n\n6. **Social Media & Networking**:\n   - **Facebook Groups**: There are various groups dedicated to remote jobs and freelancing where postings are shared frequently.\n   - **Twitter**: Following relevant hashtags like #RemoteWork, #FreelanceJobs, or #WorkFromHome can lead you to job postings.\n\n7. **Company Career Pages**:\n   - Directly visiting the career pages of companies you are interested in can yield job listings that may not be advertised on job boards.\n\nBefore applying for jobs, make sure to research the companies and read reviews to avoid scams. Look for flexible work options, and set clear expectations regarding pay and hours.",
